  -flightgear-2.8.0.ebuild:
  Remove simgear-2.8 and flightgear-2.8. Both in tree now

*flightgear-2.8.0 (17 Aug 2012)

  17 Aug 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de>
  -flightgear-2.6.0.ebuild, +flightgear-2.8.0.ebuild:
  version bump to 2.8.0.
  Uses dynamic linking now

  07 Jul 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  [dev-games/simgear,games-simulation/flightgear,games-utils/terragear-cs]
  compile with dynamic linking.
  Only for the live versions for now.

  02 Jul 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de>
  flightgear-2.6.0.ebuild, flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  add an elog informing about launchers

  27 Jun 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] use own .desktop file

  12 Jun 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999 and deps] add a second git server
  as fallback and set the name of the local clone to make sure the same
  directory is used for both server checkouts

  07 Jun 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de>
  flightgear-2.6.0.ebuild:
  [dev-games/simgear-2.6.0, games-simulation/flightgear-2.6.0] mark ~x86,
  according to feedback,
  move FG to EAPI 4

  31 May 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] switch to EAPI4 and back to official GIT url

  10 May 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de> flightgear-9999.ebuild:
  9999] larcsim/UIUC FDMs depend on each other. so get this right.

  25 Apr 2012; Christian Schmitt <chris@ilovelinux.de>
  flightgear-2.6.0.ebuild:
  2.6.0] remove larcsim and UIUC FDM useflags
  and disable them. They don't compile and are in the live ebuild only for
  the sake of completeness.
  Also, change the SRC_URI to use the mirror infrastructure. Thanks repoman :)

